Add a Skill Requirement Action

Add skill requirements to your work items to ensure the work is routed to the best agent for the customerâ€™s issue. You can add up to 10 skills with the Add Skill Requirements action and can define 20 skills overall in the flow when routing an individual work item.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

Follow these steps:

1. Drag the Add Skill Requirements action onto the canvas.
2. Give the action a label and API name and optionally, a description.
3. Under Set Input Values, optionally select a skillList variable that you created.
4. Under Add Skill Requirement, enter the skills or a variable with the Skill IDs that the agent needs.

Initially, Omni-Channel tries to route work to an agent with all the requested skills. If an agent with all the skills isn't available and additional skills are configured to be dropped, Omni-Channel drops additional skills after a timeout. Skills are dropped in order of priority, with higher priority skills being dropped first. The work item is then routed to the best-matched agent.

If an agent declines work or goes offline, the required skills reset to what they were originally, and the timer resets. A subsequent Route Work action can use the output from your Add Skill Requirements action to define skills that agents need for work items.
title: Configuring Skill Requirements for Omni-Channel Flows
